2%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Fbiz%2Fnews%2Fnelson-peltz-matchmaker-donald-trump-elon-musk-1236209437%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Some%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20scrutinized%20Nvidia's%20attempt%20to%20dodge%20a%20securities%20fraud%20lawsuit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20illustration%20of%20Jensen%20Huang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d98884a0ff598b26647fac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJensen%20Huang%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Nvidia.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FDavid%20Zalubowski%2C%20File%3B%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20heard%20Nvidia's%20arguments%20against%20a%20class%20action%20securities%20fraud%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENvidia%20is%20accused%20of%20misleading%20shareholders%20about%20cryptocurrency%20mining-related%20sales.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company's%20lawyers%20argue%20plaintiffs%20have%20not%20met%20pleading%20standards%20set%20by%20a%201995%20law.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%20heard%20arguments%20in%20a%20case%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-ceo-ai-employees-workers-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20trying%20to%20dodge%20a%20securities%20fraud%20lawsuit%20brought%20by%20shareholders.%20But%20some%20of%20the%20justices%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20chip%20giant's%20assertions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia%20petitioned%20the%20nation's%20highest%20court%20after%20a%20lower%20court%20permitted%20a%202018%20class%20action%20lawsuit%20alleging%20that%20the%20company%20and%20its%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-huang-softbank-masayoshi-son-tech-stock-buyout-ai-microchips-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJensen%20Huang%3C%2Fa%3E%20misled%20investors%20about%20its%20cryptocurrency%20mining-related%20sales%20to%20move%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20Nvidia%20argue%20that%20the%20plaintiffs%20in%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20led%20by%20a%20Swedish%20investment%20management%20firm%2C%20have%20not%20met%20the%20stricter%20pleading%20standards%20laid%20out%20by%20the%201995%20Private%20Securities%20Litigation%20Reform%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20by%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit%20to%20allow%20the%20lawsuit%20to%20proceed%20%26quot%3Bcreates%20an%20easy%20road%20map%20for%20plaintiffs%20to%20evade%20the%20Reform%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20Nvidia%20attorney%20Neal%20Katyal%20argued%20before%20the%20justices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Private%20Securities%20Litigation%20Reform%20Act%20or%20PSLRA%20was%20designed%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20curtail%20frivolous%20securities%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20stock%20drops%2C%20all%20they%20have%20to%20do%20is%20find%20an%20expert%20with%20numbers%20that%20contradict%20the%20company's%20public%20statements%2C%20then%20allege%20the%20company%20keeps%20records%20that%20executives%20look%20at%2C%20and%20then%20argue%20those%20records%20would%20have%20matched%20the%20hired%20expert's%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Katyal%2C%20who%20argued%20that%20the%20plaintiff's%20complaint%20relies%20on%20expert%20opinion%20and%20lacks%20company%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20by%20Justice%20Clarence%20Thomas%20what%20the%20plaintiff's%20complaint%20would%20look%20like%20in%20order%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20PSLRA%2C%20Katyal%20said%20it%20would%20have%20to%20answer%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20did%20the%20CEO%20know%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20did%20he%20know%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20my%20concern%20is%20that%20you%20appear%20to%20be%20requiring%20for%20plaintiffs%20to%20actually%20have%20the%20evidence%20in%20order%20to%20plead%20their%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Justice%20Ketanji%20Brown%20Jackson%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3Bpart%20of%20my%20concern%20is%20that%20you%20seem%20to%20be%20wanting%20a%20bright%20line%20that%20says%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20documents%20are%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustice%20Sonia%20Sotomayer%20said%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bconcerned%26quot%3B%20by%20Nvidia's%20petition%20to%20the%20court%20and%20told%20Katyal%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20often%20don't%20grant%20cert%20to%20error%20correct.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20actually%20sure%20what%20rule%20we%20could%20articulate%20that%20would%20be%20clearer%20than%20our%20cases%20already%20say%2C%26quot%3B%20Sotomayer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20John%20Roberts%20said%20the%20aspect%20that%20concerned%20him%20about%20both%20sides'%20arguments%20was%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20black%20and%20white.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20think%20that%20the%20positions%20on%20both%20sides%20are%20a%20little%20too%20absolute%2C%20how%20do%20you%20find%20sort%20of%20the%20sweet%20spot%20in%20terms%20of%20when%20the%20PSLRA%20is%20satisfied%3F%26quot%3B%20Roberts%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can't%20be%20just%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20direct%20evidence%20because%20that%20statute%20was%20intended%20to%20do%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Roberts%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20me%2C%20you%20can't%20insist%20on%20only%20the%20direct%20evidence%20before%20a%20complaint%20goes%20forward.%20So%20if%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20black%20and%20white%2C%20how%20do%20I%20decide%20where%20the%20balance%20is%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Nvidia%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bappreciated%20the%20opportunity%20to%20answer%20the%20Court's%20detailed%20questions%20this%20morning.%20We%20brought%20this%20case%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20protect%20shareholders%20and%20the%20economy%20from%20groundless%20lawsuits%2C%20and%20look%20forward%20to%20the%20Court's%20resolution%20of%20this%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20arguments%2C%20Deepak%20Gupta%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20said%20the%20PSLRA%20%26quot%3Bdemands%20particularity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20agrees%20you%20can't%20circumvent%20the%20statute%20with%20conclusory%20allegations%20or%20unsubstantiated%20expert%20opinions%2C%26quot%3B%20Gupta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20not%20what%20happened%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gupta.%20%26quot%3BOn%20falsity%2C%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20holding%20expressly%20rested%20on%20a%20combination%20of%20facts%20showing%20that%20a%20substantial%20part%20of%20gaming%20revenues%20came%20from%20crypto.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20included%20accounts%20from%20former%20employees%2C%20detailed%20accounts%20of%20internal%20data%20and%20meetings%2C%20expert%20analysis%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BHuang's%20eventual%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20crypto%20hangover%2C%20which%20sent%20the%20stock%20tumbling%2028%25%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20district%20court%20previously%20dismissed%20the%20plaintiffs'%20class%20action%20lawsuit%20and%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit%20reversed%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20allege%20in%20their%20brief%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20in%202017%20when%20Nvidia's%20sales%20of%20graphic%20processing%20units%20(GPUs)%20were%20surging%2C%20the%20company%20and%20Huang%20%26quot%3Bknew%20those%20record%20sales%20were%20due%20in%20substantial%20part%20to%20demand%20from%20cryptocurrency%20miners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20for%20more%20than%20a%20year%2C%20Huang%20denied%20that%20mining-related%20sales%20were%20driving%20NVIDIA's%20revenue%20growth%20because%20he%20knew%20that%20the%20securities%20market%20looked%20askew%20at%20GPU%20sales%20to%20miners%2C%20which%20are%20notoriously%20cyclical%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20brief%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHuang's%20strategy%20fell%20apart%20in%20late%202018%2C%20when%20cryptocurrency%20prices%20collapsed%2C%20GPU%20purchases%20by%20miners%20withered%2C%20and%20demand%20for%20GeForce%20GPUs%20shrank%20dramatically%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20brief%20says.%20%26quot%3BNVIDIA%20then%20finally%20admitted%20that%20%E2%80%94%20contrary%20to%20Huang's%20previous%20denials%E2%80%94its%20record%20revenue%20growth%20had%20been%20largely%20due%20to%20mining-related%20demand%20for%20GeForce%20GPUs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENvidia's%20attorneys%20argued%20in%20its%20petition%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20on%20public%20calls%20with%20investors%2C%20company%20executives%20%26quot%3Bmade%20clear%20that%20they%20believed%20crypto%20miners%20were%20buying%20both%20GeForce%20GPUs%20and%20Crypto%20SKUs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20case%20aptly%20demonstrates%20the%20danger%20of%20allowing%20plaintiffs%20to%20guess%20at%20the%20pleading%20stage%20what%20internal%20company%20reports%20could%20have%20said%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20petition%20says.%20%26quot%3BPlaintiffs%20speculate%20that%20internal%20NVIDIA%20sales%20reports%20would%20have%20reflected%20the%20amount%20of%20gaming%20segment%20revenue%20driven%20by%20sales%20to%20miners%20rather%20than%20to%20gamers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20is%20no%20basis%20in%20Plaintiffs'%20allegations%20to%20assume%20that%20this%20information%20was%20available%20to%20NVIDIA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Nvidia%20agreed%20to%20pay%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20%245.5%20million%20to%20settle%20charges%20for%20%26quot%3Binadequate%20disclosures%26quot%3B%20regarding%20the%20impact%20of%20crypto%20mining%20on%20the%20company's%20gaming%20business.%20Nvidia%20agreed%20to%20pay%20the%20penalty%20without%20admitting%20or%20denying%20the%20SEC's%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decision%20from%20t